cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE

This paper deals with energy efficiency in computing, which is a cross-cutting concern in computer science. However, the methodology proposed involves modeling power consumption and application performance, which suggests a focus on architecture and performance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Architecture), followed by cs.PF (Performance), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
